// solving a linear elliptic PDE using the second-order centered differ- //
// ences on a uniform grid.  Details of the actual algorithm have been   //
// omitted, and some steps aren't even given as comments.  For example,  //
// you'll have to insert code to implement either Point-Jacobi or        //
// Point-Gauss-Seidel to solve the pentadiagonal linear system and to    //
// determine |e|max at each iteration.  Moreover, some variables have    //
// been set to random numbers.  Some print statements are missing.  The  //
// functions that produce the BC data need updating, as do the functions //
// that produce the PDE's RHS of the analytical solution.                //
